# PydanticAI Orchestrator Skeleton

Initial orchestrator skeleton with:
- Telegram input frontend
- Hermes worker adapter
- Pi worker adapter
- Stokowski workflow adapter
- PydanticAI controller agent
- Simple routing policy
- Multi-worker mock execution
- Review loop scaffold

This first version is intentionally small and testable. By default all adapters run in `mock` mode so you can verify the structure before wiring real CLIs and workflow files.

Project layout:
- `src/pydanticai_orchestrator/settings.py` — env-based config
- `src/pydanticai_orchestrator/agent.py` — PydanticAI orchestrator agent
- `src/pydanticai_orchestrator/service.py` — routing policy + multi-worker + review loop scaffold
- `src/pydanticai_orchestrator/adapters/` — Hermes / Pi / Stokowski integrations
- `src/pydanticai_orchestrator/telegram_bot.py` — Telegram polling bot with command routing
- `docs/architecture.md` — current architecture + LangGraph upgrade path
- `tests/` — smoke tests using stdlib `unittest`

## Install into the existing venv

```bash
source /home/weiyiacc/.venvs/pydanticai/bin/activate
uv pip install -e /home/weiyiacc/projects/pydanticai-orchestrator
```

## Environment

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` or export vars in shell.

Key defaults:
- `ORCH_MODEL=test` — safe local smoke-test model
- `ORCH_HERMES_MODE=mock`
- `ORCH_PI_MODE=mock`
- `ORCH_STOKOWSKI_MODE=mock`

## Local smoke tests

```bash
source /home/weiyiacc/.venvs/pydanticai/bin/activate
cd /home/weiyiacc/projects/pydanticai-orchestrator
python -m unittest discover -s tests -v
```

## CLI examples

```bash
source /home/weiyiacc/.venvs/pydanticai/bin/activate
pydanticai-orchestrator doctor
pydanticai-orchestrator worker hermes "analyze auth module"
pydanticai-orchestrator worker pi "review data pipeline assumptions"
pydanticai-orchestrator stokowski dry-run
pydanticai-orchestrator stokowski status
pydanticai-orchestrator route "compare hermes and pi on this repo"
pydanticai-orchestrator prompt "Use Hermes for coding analysis and summarize the result"
```

## Telegram

```bash
source /home/weiyiacc/.venvs/pydanticai/bin/activate
export TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=...your token...
export ORCH_MODEL=test
pydanticai-orchestrator-telegram
```

Telegram commands:
- `/doctor`
- `/hermes <task>`
- `/pi <task>`
- `/stokowski_status`
- `/stokowski_dryrun`
- `/route <request>`

## Wiring real backends later

- Hermes: set `ORCH_HERMES_MODE=real`
- Pi: set `ORCH_PI_MODE=real`
- Stokowski: set `ORCH_STOKOWSKI_MODE=real` and `ORCH_STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=/path/to/workflow.yaml`

This skeleton is intentionally staged so you can validate the frontends and control flow first, then turn on real worker execution one backend at a time.
